{"id":1146701674,"question_id":13,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"4 months, 4 weeks","timestamp":1705307531,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"5 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1146701674/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Roman to Integer","memory":"44.5 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public int romanToInt(String s) {\n        int len = s.length();\n        \n        int[] arr = new int[len+1];\n        HashMap<Character, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();\n        map.put('I', 1);\n        map.put('V', 5);\n        map.put('X', 10);\n        map.put('L', 50);\n        map.put('C', 100);\n        map.put('D', 500);\n        map.put('M', 1000);\n        \n        int res =0 ;\n        for(int i=0; i<len; i++){\n            arr[i] = map.get(s.charAt(i));\n        }\n        \n        for(int i=0; i<len-1; i++){\n            if(arr[i+1]>arr[i]){\n                res-=arr[i];\n            }else{\n                res+=arr[i];\n            }\n        }\n        \n        return res+arr[len-1];\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"roman-to-integer","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
